When you went to get a mortgage on your house you promised to pay the bank 100 oz of Gold and pledged your house as collateral. In exchange the Bank promises to pay you 100 oz of Gold On Demand by either giving you bank notes or a balance in your checking account. They never actually gave you the gold you supposedly borrowed from the bank and instead played a fancy game of IOU swapping. An IOU from the bank is worth more than a personal IOU and therefore the bank charges you interest. The bank also demands collateral because they need to have the ability to make good on their IOU or there will be a bank run.
